President Biden held a press conference in the East Room to discuss the passing of the Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act by the United States Senate. He expressed gratitude to the bipartisan group of senators who worked on the legislation and thanked them for keeping their word. The President emphasized that this bill is a historic investment in the nation's infrastructure and will create millions of jobs, modernize roads and bridges, replace lead pipes, provide affordable high-speed internet, upgrade the power grid, and more. He highlighted that this bill will benefit working families and generate long-term economic growth. President Biden also addressed other topics, such as the resignation of Governor Andrew Cuomo, the COVID-19 Delta variant, and the situation in Afghanistan. He expressed confidence in the passage of the infrastructure bill in the House of Representatives and discussed his plans for future legislation, including voting reform and police reform. The President emphasized the importance of listening to different views and working together to achieve progress.